ranch also controls the executive branch.  In the United States there is usually a division on power because you have the house, senate, and presidency that can all be controlled by different parties.  Even then, when the senate is controlled by one party, the minority can pretty much cockblock anything unless they drop under 40 seats.<br>
<br>
The US government is designed to be inherently conservative.  By conservative in this conext I mean that it does not change, not that it is right wing.  It takes a great majority to be able to pass any law changing the statis quo.<br>
<br>
This can be good or bad, but I think it's good for the most part.  It prevents large swings in the policy of the United States.<br>
